[SN]TITLE[SN]
Managerless Inter into top half with late treble

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Managerless Inter Milan scored three late goals to climb into the top half of Serie A with an unconvincing victory over promoted Crotone.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Inter, who sacked Frank De Boer on Tuesday, went in front with six minutes left as Ivan Perisic gathered a Mauro Icardi pass and drove into the corner.
Icardi scored the second with a penalty, awarded when he was fouled by Gian Marco Ferrari.
The Argentine striker scored again three minutes into stoppage time.
